To run your Django app on a custom port, use:

  python manage.py runserver <port>

  For example:
  - python manage.py runserver 8080 - runs on port 8080
  - python manage.py runserver 3000 - runs on port 3000
  - python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:5000 - runs on port 5000 and allows external
  connections

  The default port is 8000 if not specified.